HEADWORD: chanar
<hw>chanar</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a thorny shrub or small tree
(<spn>Geoffroea decorticans</spn>) common in central Argentina having
small orange or yellow flowers followed by edible berries.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chanal, <spn>Geoffroea decorticans</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
